<br>
Full explaination if ya like:<br>
<br>
Each page of hotkeys is the exact same page. The only difference is that EQ reads your .opt file to find out what values are for what page.<br>
<br>
Everytime you &quot;flip&quot; to the next page, EQ loads those values in.<br>
<br>
Thus, giving you the illusion of 10 pages.<br>
<br>
I bet VI would have gone 12-14+ if it wasn't for the fact there's only 10 number keys ( Shift-# to switch ).<br>
